               <floruit when="1200" evidence="internal">He was a 13th century metropolitan of the Ethiopian Orothodox Church and a contemporary of King 
                  <persName ref="PRS6152Lalibala">Lālibalā </persName> 
                  who was consecrated by the then Egyptian  patriarch <persName ref="PRS5703JohnVI">John VI</persName> in <date>1200</date>. 
                  However, he was back in <placeName ref="wd:Q85"/> after five years 
                  accusing <persName ref="PRS6859MasqalK">Masqal Kǝbrā</persName> who favoured to consecrate her brother <persName ref="PRS5261hayrun">Ḫayrūn</persName>, a bishop of the city of the King.
                  He was a successor of <persName ref="PRS7072Mikael">Mikāʾel I</persName>. 
               </floruit>
         
